{"body": "@razielgn thanks for working on this.\r\n\r\nDepending on exact text for exception messages is unfortunate. MRI exception messages are often cryptic or could be improved. Other Ruby implementations should be free to improve the messages. The actual exception message should be for human consumption and should not alter the result of computation. The exception class or kind is the thing that has semantic meaning for code.\r\n\r\nFWIW, RubySpec does not specify the exception message (with rare, and probably vanishing, exception).", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21203243", "created_at": "2013-07-18T18:13:48Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11494#issuecomment-21203243", "updated_at": "2013-07-18T18:13:48Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11494, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/brixen", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/a8e44ce1b57c2689d5a7172d15df42b5?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F3ef815416f775098fe977004015c6193.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/received_events", "gravatar_id": "a8e44ce1b57c2689d5a7172d15df42b5", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "brixen", "type": "User", "id": 85, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brixen/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523c6f19bd354364b9000db5"}, "id": 21203243, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11494"}
